headline: IQVIA’s Q3 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: IQVIA's third quarter results reflected stable operational execution, with revenue and profit slightly ahead of Wall Street expectations. Management identified robust free cash flow generation and a healthy pipeline of clinical trial bookings as primary contributors to the quarter’s performance. CEO Ari Bousbib emphasized improvements in industry demand, noting that net bookings in the clinical segment grew 13% year over year, while the company’s backlog reached $32.4 billion.
